net.hudup.core.data.ctx

Interface ContextValue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ContextValueImpl

    public interface ContextValue
extends java.io.Serializable, Cloneable
    This class represents a value of context template. It has two kinds of value: quantized value (real number) and normal value (object). As a convention, this class is called context value. In general, a context represented by Context is composed of context template represented by ContextTemplate and context value represented by ContextValue. In general, context value is anything.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
